<h2>Bindings</h2>
<h4>Mut Helper</h4>
<p>
  The <code>mut</code> helper is a simple way to update a property on the container component while maintaining the benefits of DDAU.
</p>
<div class="default-style text-labels">
	<table class="demo-table">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<div class="default-theme">
					{{x-toggle
            offLabel='Hey:hey'
            onLabel='Ho:ho'
            showLabels=true
            value=boundValue
            onToggle=(mut boundValue)
          }}
				</div>
			</td>

			<td>
				value: {{input value=boundValue}}
			</td>
      <td>
        <pre><code>\{{x-toggle value=boundValue offLabel="Hey:hey" onLabel="Ho:ho" onToggle=(mut boundValue)}}</code></pre>
      </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>
				<div class="default-theme">
					{{x-toggle
            offLabel='Hey:hey'
            onLabel='Ho:ho'
            showLabels=true
            value=bV2
            onToggle=(mut bV2)
          }}
				</div>
			</td>
			<td>
				value: {{bV2}}
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
</div>

<h4>Action Helper</h4>
<table class='condensed'>
  <tr>
    <td style='width: 50%; vertical-align: top'>
      The <code>action</code> helper returns a hash of values in the structure defined to the right. Also note, if you return the boolean value of <code>false</code> to "suggestion" then the component will disable itself. Suggestions are sent when the value is not a valid value.
      <p>
        <b>Note:</b> if you open the developer console you'll see the action push it's payload to the console.
      </p>
    </td>
    <td style='vertical-align: top'>
      <pre><code>{
  code: 'toggled',
  newValue: &lt;value>,
  oldValue: &lt;value>,
  context: &lt;object>
}</code></pre>
    </td>
    <td style='vertical-align: top'>
      <pre><code>{
  code: 'suggestion',
  newValue: &lt;value>,
  oldValue: &lt;value>,
  context: &lt;object>
}</code></pre>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

